00:01:42.410 --> 00:01:52.630
Umamusume

00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:52.670
Pretty Derby

00:02:56.030 --> 00:03:00.050
Episode 7
Our Arima Kinen

00:02:58.530 --> 00:03:00.540
Who'd you vote for in the Arima?

00:03:00.530 --> 00:03:02.530
Arima Kinen Fan Vote

00:03:00.540 --> 00:03:02.530
Kitasan Black and Cheval Grand.

00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:05.030
Yeah, those two are the top
choices in the senior class.

00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:07.740
But in the classics group,
it's gotta be Satono Diamond!

00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:09.910
She was amazing at the Kikkashou!

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:14.570
She's always had potential, but
she had that string of bad luck.

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:17.610
They're both the representatives
for their generations,

00:03:17.610 --> 00:03:19.920
so seeing them against each
other should be something.

00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:30.470
Third place in the Japan Cup.
You almost had it.

00:03:30.470 --> 00:03:32.650
You put up a great fight, though! Congrats!

00:03:33.040 --> 00:03:34.770
Well, sure...

00:03:34.770 --> 00:03:38.330
Y'know, it feels like it's been a
while since the three of us met up.

00:03:38.330 --> 00:03:41.920
The other day we were celebrating my
win, but Chevacchi couldn't make it.

00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:43.920
I had other plans...

00:03:43.920 --> 00:03:45.280
You did?

00:03:46.130 --> 00:03:49.970
It's wonderful that you won the last
tiara at the Shuukashou, Vivlos.

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:52.560
Well, I can't be like you,

00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:55.550
getting beat by Gentil-san and ending
up in second place all the time!

00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:57.720
Oh, you want to go there?

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:00.920
The Arima is next for you, right, Cheval?

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:02.930
Yeah, I guess.

00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:05.930
You should get your first G1
win at the Arima, Chevacchi!

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:09.500
It'd be nice if all three
of us could have G1 wins.

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:10.930
Sure would!

00:04:10.930 --> 00:04:14.060
Let's eat something tasty today
and then get back to practice.

00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:13.530
My older sister got second place
in all the Triple Tiara races,

00:04:13.530 --> 00:04:15.770
and has won the Victoria Mile
multiple times.

00:04:14.060 --> 00:04:15.770
Yeah! Let's do it!

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:19.530
Even my younger sister, Vivlos,
won a G1 race before me.

00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:18.110
Wow...

00:04:20.290 --> 00:04:23.450
I'm the only one with nothing to show yet.

00:04:24.170 --> 00:04:25.430
I can't lose again!

00:04:24.470 --> 00:04:27.160
Chevacchi, if you're not
gonna eat yours, I'll take it.

00:04:25.690 --> 00:04:27.910
Not to anyone else!

00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:31.790
Fukunaga Shopping District

00:04:30.250 --> 00:04:33.160
Okay, and that's that!

00:04:33.160 --> 00:04:35.620
Thanks again, Kita-chan.

00:04:35.620 --> 00:04:39.230
Feels kinda bad, making a horse girl with
three G1 wins help us out like that.

00:04:39.230 --> 00:04:42.160
Oh, come on, don't worry about that!

00:04:42.160 --> 00:04:45.110
Hey, Kita-chan! Congrats on the Japan Cup!

00:04:45.110 --> 00:04:46.490
Thank you so much!

00:04:46.490 --> 00:04:49.540
I voted for you in the fan poll, Kita-chan.

00:04:49.540 --> 00:04:51.050
Good luck at the Arima!

00:04:51.050 --> 00:04:55.310
Right! I get to run with Dia-chan this
year, so I'm really looking forward to it!

00:04:55.610 --> 00:04:57.790
We'll all have to be there
to root for you again.

00:04:57.790 --> 00:05:00.680
We're looking forward to the Winning
Concert after the race, too!

00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:02.190
Whether I win or lose...

00:05:02.190 --> 00:05:04.760
Well, no, I don't intend to lose,

00:05:04.760 --> 00:05:07.080
so I'll make sure it's the
best performance possible!

00:05:07.080 --> 00:05:08.840
Yo, Kita-chan from the festival!

00:05:08.840 --> 00:05:10.490
Yo, Kita-chan from the festival!

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:12.330
Yo, Kita-chan from the festival!

00:05:12.330 --> 00:05:13.950
Yo, Kita-chan from the festival!

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:15.600
Yo, Kita-chan from the festival!

00:05:14.320 --> 00:05:17.360
Yeah! I'll make sure it's a memorable one!

00:05:15.600 --> 00:05:17.360
Yo, it's a Kita-chan festival!

00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:17.710
Yo!

00:05:17.710 --> 00:05:19.460
Goal

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:26.280
Kita-san looks pretty good.

00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:27.260
She does.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:30.910
Yeah. I'm expecting even better results
at the Arima than she had last year.

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:33.000
That's something to look forward to.

00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:37.990
Kitasan looks fearsome.

00:05:37.990 --> 00:05:39.100
Yes.

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:47.970
There...

00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:49.950
Kita-chan!

00:05:49.950 --> 00:05:52.020
You doing anything after this?

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:53.910
Oh, not really.

00:05:53.910 --> 00:05:56.960
In that case, come hang with me for a bit.

00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:08.970
Tasty!

00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:08.970
Delicious!

00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:10.780
You seem to be doing pretty well.

00:06:10.780 --> 00:06:13.460
Yeah! I've been feeling so excited.

00:06:13.460 --> 00:06:17.760
I must be excited to be running
at the Arima Kinen with Dia-chan.

00:06:17.760 --> 00:06:18.980
I see.

00:06:19.230 --> 00:06:21.340
It's all because of you, y'know.

00:06:21.340 --> 00:06:22.410
Me?

00:06:22.410 --> 00:06:23.400
Yeah.

00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:30.770
Your Arima Kinen win was incredible. Truly.

00:06:31.230 --> 00:06:36.000
You grabbed everyone's attention,
and when you crossed the goal,

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.200
it was like the entire track
started to light up and shine...

00:06:40.650 --> 00:06:43.990
I saw it in that moment.

00:06:44.420 --> 00:06:48.720
It was the same kind of stage that
could create a star like my Dad...

00:06:49.280 --> 00:06:52.590
Glamorous and beautiful,
like something out of a dream

00:06:52.590 --> 00:06:55.160
that grabs the heart and never lets go.

00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:58.810
So, we made a promise.

00:06:59.310 --> 00:07:03.930
That one day, we'd run together
on a big stage like that.

00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:09.540
That we'd give it everything we had in an
amazing race like the one we saw that day.

00:07:11.450 --> 00:07:15.290
Dia-chan's been my friend
for such a long time now.

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:19.710
Whenever only one of us had something,
we'd split it between us.

00:07:20.490 --> 00:07:25.710
But there's no sharing first place
at Arima, and we can't split it, either.

00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:29.130
The same Arima Kinen I was
frustrated at last year.

00:07:29.450 --> 00:07:31.730
Since then, I've trained a
whole bunch, I've worked hard,

00:07:31.730 --> 00:07:34.470
I've won, and I've built myself up.

00:07:34.720 --> 00:07:40.280
When we were little, I could never beat
Dia-chan in footraces or at jumping rope.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:45.550
But this time, in this race,
I'm going to win!

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:47.380
Looks like you're doing fine.

00:07:48.730 --> 00:07:50.510
I was wondering,

00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:53.990
since being in good shape doesn't mean
you're doing great mentally, sometimes.

00:07:54.630 --> 00:07:55.970
Teio-san...

00:07:56.490 --> 00:07:58.470
Good luck, Kita-chan.

00:07:58.470 --> 00:07:59.590
Right!

00:07:59.590 --> 00:08:02.990
I'd like to win the Arima Kinen
and start being considered

00:08:02.990 --> 00:08:06.930
the star horse girl of my generation!

00:08:08.490 --> 00:08:10.510
Maybe I'm getting carried away?

00:08:13.510 --> 00:08:16.510
Hong Kong G1 Victory Celebration

00:08:16.510 --> 00:08:19.010
Hong Kong G1 Victory Celebration

00:08:23.280 --> 00:08:26.680
I didn't think your first G1 victory
would be in an overseas race.

00:08:27.810 --> 00:08:30.860
Yeah, I thought the same thing. But...

00:08:31.070 --> 00:08:33.160
After winning, I finally understood.

00:08:33.530 --> 00:08:36.870
Just how significant and
joyful it is to win a G1 race.

00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:38.130
Crown-chan...

00:08:38.130 --> 00:08:40.370
And maybe that's thanks to you, Dia.

00:08:40.620 --> 00:08:44.990
When you won the Kikkashou,
you broke the Satono jinx.

00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:46.250
It's not like that...

00:08:46.520 --> 00:08:50.290
Lately, a lot of the other Satono
girls have been doing well, right?

00:08:50.290 --> 00:08:55.010
And some of them are talking about
you creating a whole new jinx.

00:08:55.520 --> 00:08:58.890
I guess I'll have to disprove that one next.

00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:04.430
Still, thank you, Dia.

00:09:04.430 --> 00:09:08.950
The fact is, your efforts at the
Kikkashou definitely lit a fire in me.

00:09:08.950 --> 00:09:10.410
It's fine, Crown-chan...

00:09:10.410 --> 00:09:12.480
I could say the same thing to you.

00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:16.980
I want to be like you, too.

00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:20.080
I'm thinking of taking on
some global races next year.

00:09:21.390 --> 00:09:23.450
So, in this Arima Kinen...

00:09:23.450 --> 00:09:26.710
There's someone I absolutely need to beat.

00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:29.260
You mean Kitasan?

00:09:30.300 --> 00:09:32.850
You mentioned how you promised
each other to race at the Arima

00:09:32.850 --> 00:09:34.700
when you were little.

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:37.720
That's a big part of it. But...

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:41.320
By winning against the person
I think is the strongest right now,

00:09:41.320 --> 00:09:43.260
I'll prove I'm the best in Japan.

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:46.870
Then I can move onto representing
the country as I pursue

00:09:46.870 --> 00:09:50.230
ultimate glory for the Satono family.

00:09:50.710 --> 00:09:52.590
With my own hands.

00:09:54.350 --> 00:09:55.340
Dia...

00:09:56.990 --> 00:10:00.990
Umamusume

00:09:56.990 --> 00:10:00.990
Pretty Derby

00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:09.830
Looking good, Earth-chan!

00:10:10.740 --> 00:10:13.130
No problems here. I'm feeling
as leggiero as can be!

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:15.160
So, you think you can win the Arima?

00:10:15.160 --> 00:10:17.880
It won't be a problem, Mademoiselle Nature.

00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.650
I can guarantee you this:

00:10:20.650 --> 00:10:24.390
I will run in a fashion comparable
to Gold Ship's spectacular performance!

00:10:24.610 --> 00:10:27.100
Golshi-san got eighth place
last year, didn't she?

00:10:27.100 --> 00:10:27.930
That's no good!

00:10:27.930 --> 00:10:30.350
Yes, but eroicamente!

00:10:30.350 --> 00:10:34.500
I have no idea what that means,
but you seem confident!

00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:36.270
It's Kitasan Black!

00:10:37.860 --> 00:10:40.010
Kitasan seems to have a
lot of momentum as well.

00:10:40.010 --> 00:10:41.670
This could be her fourth G1 win.

00:10:41.670 --> 00:10:44.050
Yep, she's real strong.

00:10:44.050 --> 00:10:46.330
You can tell, 'cuz I said so!

00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:49.130
Her growth since the spring has been crazy.

00:10:50.110 --> 00:10:51.720
That is true...

00:10:51.720 --> 00:10:53.500
Nature-sensei!

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:55.980
I hope I can get more advice later!

00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:57.260
Sensei?

00:10:57.260 --> 00:10:58.410
Then she's...

00:10:58.410 --> 00:11:00.410
Kitasan Black's sensei?

00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:01.390
That's amazing!

00:11:01.390 --> 00:11:03.760
How come you're her sensei, Nature?

00:11:03.760 --> 00:11:05.890
Don't ask me.

00:11:18.300 --> 00:11:22.030
Man, Kitasan is pushing too hard.

00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:27.370
It's almost time to race, Dia-chan.

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:31.290
It's almost time, Kita-chan.

00:11:33.010 --> 00:11:36.920
Dia-chan, who always followed
behind me when we were little.

00:11:37.370 --> 00:11:43.430
Kita-chan, who would always take my
hand to show me all kinds of things.

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:49.180
Dia-chan, who's so talented, strong,
pretty, and cool. That's why...

00:11:51.010 --> 00:11:53.770
The stage is set, Kita-chan.

00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:57.610
I'm gonna win!

00:11:57.610 --> 00:11:59.400
I'm going to win!

00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:17.930
Hey, you still awake?

00:12:19.920 --> 00:12:21.950
Yeah, I am.

00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:26.540
Needing to sleep but being unable to...
reminds me of the night before a field trip.

00:12:26.870 --> 00:12:30.610
That reminds me of the trip
where I dropped my lunch,

00:12:30.610 --> 00:12:33.410
and then you split yours with me.

00:12:34.080 --> 00:12:35.370
Did that happen?

00:12:36.920 --> 00:12:39.820
We can't share the grand prize, though.

00:12:41.140 --> 00:12:41.880
Yeah.

00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:48.840
Dia-chan, y'know... I've always
thought you were really amazing.

00:12:49.530 --> 00:12:55.450
Even the things I started first, you would
always catch up and then surpass me.

00:12:55.830 --> 00:12:58.300
You've always been so talented...

00:12:58.300 --> 00:13:02.110
and you're kinda like a little sister,
but so cool and strong.

00:13:04.710 --> 00:13:08.500
And now I get to race against
you! I'm really excited.

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:09.960
So am I.

00:13:12.160 --> 00:13:14.250
You always work so hard, Kita-chan,

00:13:14.250 --> 00:13:19.450
and you're always so cheerful and smiling,
and you make other people happy.

00:13:20.110 --> 00:13:22.730
It makes me think about
how strong you must be.

00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:23.960
Dia-chan...

00:13:24.610 --> 00:13:27.250
We had better get some sleep. Good night.

00:13:27.840 --> 00:13:29.740
Yeah. Good night.

00:13:43.530 --> 00:13:45.000
Dia-chan?!

00:13:46.750 --> 00:13:47.980
Just a dream?

00:13:48.430 --> 00:13:50.300
Wait, what time is it?!

00:13:51.830 --> 00:13:54.140
What a relief...

00:13:54.140 --> 00:13:56.700
Huh? Where is she?

00:13:58.190 --> 00:14:01.820
I'm going on ahead
Dia

00:14:03.200 --> 00:14:07.900
I guess the race has already
kinda started, hasn't it, Dia-chan?

00:14:07.900 --> 00:14:09.480
Okay!

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:12.830
So cold...

00:14:16.680 --> 00:14:17.870
As a chilly wind blows,

00:14:17.870 --> 00:14:22.590
so too do impassioned ambitions
rise above the Nakayama Racecourse.

00:14:22.810 --> 00:14:25.520
It's that time of year again:
the Arima Kinen.

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:27.220
This should be a heck of a race.

00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:30.970
What kind of story will we see unfold
at the last grand prix of the year?

00:14:30.970 --> 00:14:33.830
There are so many people in attendance.

00:14:33.830 --> 00:14:36.150
Enough that it feels warm,
even though it's December.

00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:37.480
Yeah!

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:38.970
Here we go...

00:14:39.850 --> 00:14:40.730
They're coming out.

00:14:42.980 --> 00:14:45.780
In the fan vote before the race,
Kitasan Black came in first.

00:14:45.780 --> 00:14:48.860
But Satono Diamond is the
favorite to win it, apparently.

00:14:48.860 --> 00:14:50.530
Who are you rooting for?

00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:53.160
You're seriously asking? You should know.

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:54.910
Kitasan Black

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:54.910
Satono Diamond

00:14:55.420 --> 00:14:56.770
It was a silly question.

00:14:57.540 --> 00:15:01.000
I'd say all attention has to be on these two.

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:02.120
Correct.

00:15:02.120 --> 00:15:04.790
After her long-awaited G1
victory at the Kikkashou,

00:15:04.790 --> 00:15:08.800
she's earned a reputation as the strongest
among the classics group, Satono Diamond!

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:15.230
Versus the winner of the previous year's
Kikkashou, with three G1 wins to her name,

00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:17.560
Kitasan Black, defending her
position in the senior class!

00:15:17.560 --> 00:15:19.680
The final grand prix of the year...

00:15:19.680 --> 00:15:22.560
Which I suppose makes this
an air on the string of G.

00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.820
I can't run another pathetic race.

00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:32.550
Not in front of them. Never again.

00:15:34.010 --> 00:15:36.330
The race is just about to begin.

00:15:44.650 --> 00:15:45.720
Dia-chan.

00:15:46.930 --> 00:15:48.900
Dia-chan, let's have...

00:15:58.720 --> 00:16:02.320
Let's have a good race, fair and square!

00:16:10.010 --> 00:16:13.150
I'm going to win, Kitasan Black.

00:16:24.940 --> 00:16:27.610
Dia-chan's really focused...

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:29.610
I'd better be, too.

00:16:51.340 --> 00:16:53.280
How do these 100,000 cheers

00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:57.620
resonate in the ears of the horse
girls as they head to the starting line?

00:16:57.930 --> 00:16:59.650
They continue to enter their gates.

00:16:59.650 --> 00:17:04.500
What kind of race—what kind of drama are
we about to see unfold at the Arima Kinen?

00:17:05.510 --> 00:17:07.160
And they're off.

00:17:07.160 --> 00:17:09.670
Kitasan Black is running on
the inside after a good start.

00:17:09.670 --> 00:17:11.920
All Haiyu is following her
lead, running next to her.

00:17:13.170 --> 00:17:14.470
Go!

00:17:14.680 --> 00:17:18.320
In the struggle for first place,
Read Fantasy is pushing hard early.

00:17:18.320 --> 00:17:20.260
Kitasan Black is right behind her.

00:17:20.260 --> 00:17:22.430
Satono Diamond is in the middle of the pack,

00:17:22.430 --> 00:17:24.430
but you can see her green
racing dress moving up.

00:17:24.430 --> 00:17:27.450
And the horse girls are greeted
with 100,000 cheers

00:17:27.450 --> 00:17:30.690
as they round the fourth corner of the
first lap, now in the first home stretch.

00:17:30.960 --> 00:17:34.460
Read Fantasy is in the lead, with Kitasan
Black uncontested in second place,

00:17:34.460 --> 00:17:37.610
followed by All Haiyu and Great House.

00:17:37.610 --> 00:17:39.180
Listen to that...

00:17:39.180 --> 00:17:40.960
That's the Arima for you.

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:41.950
For real.

00:17:41.950 --> 00:17:45.030
Not bad, but don't fall for it, Kitasan.

00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:47.050
As they enter the first corner,

00:17:47.050 --> 00:17:49.530
the runners seem to be quietly
taking stock of the situation.

00:17:49.530 --> 00:17:51.620
The first 1,000 meters were
covered in 61 seconds,

00:17:51.620 --> 00:17:54.170
and Read Fantasy is running out
in front in sprightly fashion.

00:17:54.170 --> 00:17:57.470
Six to seven lengths behind her is the
number one runner, Kitasan Black.

00:17:57.470 --> 00:17:58.960
Is this too fast?

00:17:58.960 --> 00:18:02.490
No, I should be able to handle it now!

00:18:02.880 --> 00:18:07.230
And now, as if she's marked Kitasan Black,
Satono Diamond moves up into third place.

00:18:07.450 --> 00:18:11.810
Number six, Sounds of Earth,
was second place in last year's race.

00:18:10.440 --> 00:18:12.230
Earth!

00:18:12.230 --> 00:18:14.490
And number 14, Cheval Grand,
is also on the move.

00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:16.030
You can do it!

00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:19.030
Going into the third corner, there's
less than 600 meters left in the race.

00:18:19.030 --> 00:18:22.030
I can do this, I can do this, now's the time!

00:18:22.030 --> 00:18:24.060
There's very little space between
first and second place now.

00:18:24.060 --> 00:18:26.520
Kitasan Black has closed in to just
about half a length's distance!

00:18:26.520 --> 00:18:28.540
She is steadily gaining ground!

00:18:28.540 --> 00:18:31.420
She's gonna try to pass?
But it's looking good!

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:33.250
There you go, come on!

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:33.250
Keep it going!

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:33.250
Don't let 'em pass you!

00:18:33.580 --> 00:18:35.380
You can do it, Kita-chan.

00:18:35.380 --> 00:18:37.690
Rounding the fourth corner
and into the final straight!

00:18:37.690 --> 00:18:41.390
And 100,000 cheering voices once
again rumble across the turf of Nakayama.

00:18:41.710 --> 00:18:43.310
Read Fantasy seems to be struggling.

00:18:43.310 --> 00:18:44.970
Kitasan Black's lead is growing!

00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:47.270
And as if signaled by
Kitasan Black, All Haiyu,

00:18:47.270 --> 00:18:50.150
Satono Diamond, and Cheval Grand
start moving up!

00:18:50.150 --> 00:18:53.610
The most popular horse girls are
now all pushing their way forward!

00:18:58.190 --> 00:18:59.690
There! The goal!

00:19:02.720 --> 00:19:05.810
Kitasan Black is going for it!
She's begun her last spurt!

00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:06.540
Go!

00:19:05.810 --> 00:19:09.060
Will she be able to turn Nakayama
into a festival this year?!

00:19:06.330 --> 00:19:08.410
Go!

00:19:09.060 --> 00:19:10.570
But she's not gaining much!

00:19:10.570 --> 00:19:12.730
The group near the front
isn't letting her get away!

00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:16.380
Is Kitasan Black struggling?!
Satono Diamond is making her way up!

00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:19.970
She's here! But—

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:24.390
Kitasan Black pushes again!

00:19:24.620 --> 00:19:25.720
Keep going!

00:19:32.060 --> 00:19:37.730
She always passes me, but not today!

00:19:42.470 --> 00:19:44.520
Satono Diamond is moving up!

00:19:44.520 --> 00:19:46.270
She's on the tail of Kitasan Black again!

00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:47.800
All Haiyu is hanging on too!

00:19:47.800 --> 00:19:49.350
But there's Satono Diamond!

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:52.050
We're looking at a three-way battle
between the top horse girls!

00:19:52.950 --> 00:19:53.960
Keep going!

00:19:53.960 --> 00:19:55.090
Go for it!

00:19:59.370 --> 00:20:01.470
Keep going, keep going, keep going!

00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:03.320
I'm going for it!

00:20:09.210 --> 00:20:11.350
Can she make it?! Will she
make it?! Did she make it?!

00:20:11.560 --> 00:20:13.920
On the outside, and just barely!

00:20:13.920 --> 00:20:16.490
It's Satono Diamond!

00:20:16.490 --> 00:20:19.980
Satono Diamond comes out on
top in this climactic clash!

00:20:19.980 --> 00:20:24.620
She's demonstrated ability that will make
her really shine in the senior class!

00:20:30.090 --> 00:20:32.870
Eighth place, eh? Such a sweet melody.

00:20:32.870 --> 00:20:34.870
Eighth place! She tried hard!

00:21:02.940 --> 00:21:04.740
Congratulations, Dia-chan.

00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.590
Thanks, Kita-chan!

00:21:08.410 --> 00:21:11.430
You were great. I mean, really!

00:21:11.430 --> 00:21:13.700
Yeah, so were you!

00:21:13.700 --> 00:21:17.290
Guess I couldn't beat you after all!

00:21:17.770 --> 00:21:20.250
I was pretty desperate too, y'know.

00:21:20.460 --> 00:21:23.590
Since I've been chasing you
this entire time, Kita-chan.

00:21:28.550 --> 00:21:29.780
I see...

00:21:30.770 --> 00:21:33.000
Let's do a good job at the Winning Concert!

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:37.100
I told the folks from the market
I'd put on a great show for them.

00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:38.830
Sure.

00:21:52.550 --> 00:21:55.460
We've never been on stage
together like this before, huh?

00:21:55.460 --> 00:21:57.860
Yeah, it's kinda nerve-wracking.

00:21:57.860 --> 00:21:59.110
Me too.

00:21:59.110 --> 00:22:04.090
Y'know, they say if you write the
kanji for "festival" on your hand—

00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:06.060
Kita-chan, it's starting.

00:22:06.060 --> 00:22:07.130
Yeah!

00:22:12.830 --> 00:22:14.570
It was a good race, but...

00:22:14.990 --> 00:22:16.510
I'm seeing her from behind again.

